node.title: ACT records 15 new COVID-19 cases as cluster grows at Wanniassa School
node.alt: A nurse pulls up a syringe of COVID-19 vaccine.
node.description: The ACT has recorded 15 new locally acquired COVID-19 cases as the junior campus of Wanniassa School in Canberra's south closes due to a growing COVID-19 cluster.
node.content:
["The ACT has recorded 15 new locally acquired COVID-19 cases.", "There are five people in hospital with the virus, including two people\u00a0in intensive care \u2013 one person\u00a0requires\u00a0ventilation.", "93.6 per cent of Canberrans aged 12 and over have now received two doses of a COVID-19 vaccine.", "There are currently 141 active cases of COVID-19 in the territory.", "
Cluster grows at Wanniassa School
", "The junior campus of Wanniassa School in Canberra's south has been closed due to a growing COVID-19 cluster.", "An individual was unknowingly infectious with COVID-19 while at the school on October 27, 28 and 29.\u00a0", "ACT Health said there have been a number of further cases identified and advised anyone who has been on the school's junior campus since\u00a0Monday, October 25\u00a0to get tested and quarantine until they received a negative result.", "ACT Health said it was also working\u00a0closely with the Education Directorate to provide support to staff and students.", "Over the border in NSW, Queanbeyan Public School has also been closed after a member of the school community tested positive for COVID-19.", "All staff and students have been asked to self-isolate until they receive further advice.", "The school will remain closed while contract tracing and cleaning is\u00a0carried out."]
